==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bilin
<hw>Bi"lin</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>biline</ets>, from L. <ets>bilis</ets> bile.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A name applied to the amorphous or crystalline mass
obtained from bile by the action of alcohol and ether. It is composed of
a mixture of the sodium salts of the bile acids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bilinear</ent>⟦br⟧
